ow I'm going to get smacked around some, but I'm game. The question is how to lessen the burden a bit. Would it be easier to just be a halfling druid on the good team? I know the class, can travel easily, can solo almost anything (good for farming cash). Or is there another class I'm overlooking that is fairly easy to equip, can solo some, can hold their own in PvP, yet can eventually surpass the power of a druid at high levels. <br>
<br>
Kind of a lame question I guess but any comments/advice are welcome.<br>
<br>
