<br>
Firstly you can't be a good halfling druid (they are neutral only) but you can be human, half elf or wood elf. If you want a breakdown of the most powerful classes by level it would probably go like this (imo):<br>
<br>
20: Shadowknights: Most of the dmg cap is removed letting them hit you for some signifigant dmg at these levels, combined with snares and HTs make them very powerful here.<br>
<br>
30: Druids: Some people never level past 35 with their druid, they just go around ganking evils all day. Druids really shine in these levels.<br>
<br>
40: Necros: There is a point in their 40's and early 50s where necros start getting signifigant lifetaps and some fast casting ones as well.<br>
<br>
50: Bards: Around level 50 bards get 3 minute selos, poison/disease dots, good regen songs. Makes them very powerful at these levels. You need to have some skill and be willing to sacrifice your wrists.<br>
<br>
59: Rangers: With AM3 and endless quiver rangers are killing machines. Takes an insane amount of skill to bug arrows consistantly.<br>
<br>
60: Wizards: Even without MB wizards can take on almost any class and win at these levels. The best PvP AA skills of any class (rangers come close) combined with the fastest casting, hardest hitting, lowest resist nukes in the game.<br>
<br>
65: Enchanters: About the only class I am afraid of at these levels. Sure a 65 AAd SK can deathtouch players every 32 minutes but a well geared 65 enchanter will own you every minute of every day unless you do some serious prep work and blow wads of cash. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=velaelsoulrender>Velael Soulrender</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist<BR>The Snuggly SZ'r!</span><br>  Posts: 899<br> <font color=#ffffff>(12/24/02 8:58 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Best Race/Class combo for Sullon Zek</span><hr size=1> Hate had a in-guild pvp war for some bragging rights and serious chunks of cash from the guild bank. The last 2 standing in the free for all were <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27810">Nygil </a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->(65 Bard) and <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=63110">Guzzer </a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->(65 Enchanter). Those 2 are badass in their own rights, but also the class advantages at those levels are huge.<br>
